If $$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ and M = A + A<sup>2</sup> + A<sup>3</sup> + ....... + A<sup>20</sup>, then the sum of all the elements of the matrix M is equal to _____________.

questions.explanation:
$${A^n} = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; n &amp; {{{{n^2} + n} \over 2}}  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; n  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>So, required sum<br><br>$$ = 20 \times 3 + 2 \times \left( {{{20 \times 21} \over 2}} \right) + \sum\limits_{r = 1}^{20} {\left( {{{{r^2} + r} \over 2}} \right)} $$<br><br>$$ = 60 + 420 + 105 + 35 \times 41 = 2020$$
